DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;


$t[0] = 2005;
$t[1] = 2008;
$t[2] = 2012;
$f[0] = random(30,60,5);
$f[1] = random(100,160,10);
$f[2] = random(30,50,5);

$dy_a = $f[1] - $f[0];
$a = "$dy_a/3";
$dy_b = $f[2] - $f[1];
$b = "$dy_b/4";
$dy_c = $f[2] - $f[0];
$c = "$dy_c/7";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 6:
$BR $SPACE $BR
In 2005, you have $f[0] CDs in your collection.  In 2008, you have $f[1] CDs.  In 2012, you have $f[2] CDs.  What is the average rate of change in the size of your CD collection between:
$BR $SPACE $BR
a) 2005 and 2008? $SPACE $SPACE \{ ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
b) 2008 and 2012? $SPACE $SPACE \{ ans_rule(10) \}
$BR
c) 2005 and 2012? $SPACE $SPACE \{ ans_rule(10) \}

END_TEXT

ANS( num_cmp( $a ) );
ANS( num_cmp( $b ) );
ANS( num_cmp( $c ) );


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
a) Over the first interval 2005 to 2008, \( \triangle y = $f[1] - $f[0] = $dy_a \) and \( \triangle x = 2008 - 2005 = 3 \) .  Thus the average rate of change during this interval is \( \frac{ \triangle y }{ \triangle x} = \frac{ $dy_a}{3} \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) Over the interval 2008 to 2012, \( \triangle y = $f[2] - $f[1] = $dy_b \) and \( \triangle x = 2012 - 2008 = 4 \) .  Thus the average rate of change during this interval is \( \frac{ \triangle y }{ \triangle x} = \frac{ $dy_b}{4} \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) Over the interval 2005 to 2012, \( \triangle y = $f[2] - $f[0] = $dy_c \) and \( \triangle x = 2012 - 2005 = 7 \) .  Thus the average rate of change during this interval is \( \frac{ \triangle y }{ \triangle x} = \frac{ $dy_c}{7} \).
$BR 
END_SOLUTION
      
ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.